1
00:00:08,041 --> 00:00:11,041
♪

2
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:22,708
[VIDAUX] Effelsberg
electromagnetic telescope?

3
00:00:23,791 --> 00:00:26,375
Yeah, that’s the “quiet place”
she mentioned.

4
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:29,041
What is she doing there?

5
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:34,458
[DERRIDA] She’s continuing
on with our experiment.

6
00:00:34,541 --> 00:00:36,375
[YURI gasps]
But, why?

7
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:39,750
She’s trying to restore
things to the way they were.

8
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,458
Before the war.

9
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,958
[gasp]

10
00:00:43,958 --> 00:00:46,708
Can she do that?
Isn’t it dangerous, though?

11
00:00:46,791 --> 00:00:49,791
Yes. Which is why
I’m going to stop her.

12
00:00:50,791 --> 00:00:52,791
This was my task
from the beginning.

13
00:00:52,875 --> 00:00:54,291
[YURI gasps]

14
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:56,500
[YURI]
Derrida, you don’t mean...

15
00:00:56,583 --> 00:00:58,208
[gasp]

16
00:00:58,291 --> 00:00:59,458
[sigh]

17
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:01,250
[gasp]

18
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:02,916
[sigh]

19
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,875
I thought you said
that it was impossible

20
00:01:04,958 --> 00:01:06,458
to make major changes.

21
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:08,833
[DERRIDA] Only if you’re doing
uncontrolled time rides,

22
00:01:08,916 --> 00:01:10,208
in which you don’t know

23
00:01:10,291 --> 00:01:12,125
when or where you’ll
jump to in the past.

24
00:01:12,208 --> 00:01:14,833
If you can control that factor,
then I think,

25
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:16,916
-it should be doable.
-Hmm...

26
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
If you alter the past,
what about us?

27
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:21,208
Will your time traveling
change who we are today?

28
00:01:21,291 --> 00:01:23,458
Yes, any alterations
I make

29
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,250
could affect
the present as well.

30
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,291
I won’t deny that.

31
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:28,083
[gasp]

32
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:29,791
[whimper]

33
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:32,833
♪

34
00:01:32,916 --> 00:01:34,416
So depending on what you do,

35
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,416
we may no longer be
the people we are right now.

36
00:01:38,625 --> 00:01:42,166
Is our world really
that fragile? Or malleable?

37
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:45,791
My decisions aren’t all
that matter, though.

38
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:47,541
The world we live in?

39
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:50,583
It’s the sum of countless small
choices made by individuals.

40
00:01:51,625 --> 00:01:53,041
[VIDAUX]
I suppose.

41
00:01:54,958 --> 00:01:56,666
I hope even if
the world changes,

42
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,166
I can still remember you guys

43
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,833
and everything
we’ve done together.

44
00:02:00,916 --> 00:02:02,416
[gasp]

45
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:07,208
Do you really have to go
and change the past, Derrida?

46
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:08,625
Isn’t there any other way?

47
00:02:10,166 --> 00:02:13,250
I’m sorry, but it’s the only
option available to us now.

48
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:16,083
[sigh, whimper]

49
00:02:16,166 --> 00:02:17,666
-[beeping]
-Huh?

50
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:20,333
[GRAHAM] I have just received
an urgent transmission.

51
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:21,583
[beeping]

52
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:23,250
The enemy has launched

53
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:26,291
an obliteration bombing
campaign on our nation.

54
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:28,583
[ALL gasp]

55
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,458
[GRAHAM]
The target area includes

56
00:02:31,541 --> 00:02:33,291
all land within our borders.

57
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:36,875
The government is ordering
full retaliation in turn.

58
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,000
[DERRIDA groans]

59
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:40,333
What does that mean?

60
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:44,291
[DERRIDA]
Total destruction is imminent.

61
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:47,375
[clocks ticking]

62
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:54,166
[one clock ticks louder]

63
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:57,250
[one clock ticks faster]

64
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,041
[ticking in reverse]

65
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:32,958
[wind blowing]

66
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:37,458
♪

67
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:51,000
[GRAHAM] Detecting a large
number of DZs ahead.

68
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:01,291
[metal creaking]

69
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:02,500
[buzz]

70
00:05:11,625 --> 00:05:14,125
[buzzing, creaking, rumbling]

71
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:17,333
-Let’s go!
-[engine revs]

72
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,416
[tires screech]

73
00:05:23,125 --> 00:05:24,083
-Now!
-[click]

74
00:05:24,166 --> 00:05:26,083
[energy buzzing]

75
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:31,666
[buzzing continues]

76
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:33,458
[smash]

77
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,916
[BOTH groan]

78
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,000
[smashing]

79
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,166
[groaning]

80
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,791
Mage came here all by herself?

81
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:44,666
[gasp]

82
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:47,666
♪

83
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:52,416
[engine roaring]

84
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,583
[smash]

85
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:57,583
[blasting]

86
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,666
[sigh]
Damn scrap heaps!

87
00:06:08,625 --> 00:06:10,333
There you are.

88
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:18,333
[wind blowing]

89
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,166
Good, they’re not following.

90
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,250
[rumbling]

91
00:06:27,083 --> 00:06:29,083
[wind blowing]

92
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:37,416
That’s it.

93
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,541
♪

94
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:40,125
[YURI]
Have you been here before?

95
00:06:40,208 --> 00:06:42,166
[DERRIDA]
Once, when I was a student.

96
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,041
I chose it as
a potential location

97
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:46,125
for the time jump device.

98
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:50,666
To use it, you need quiet.
Total quiet.

99
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:53,375
A place that blocks
electromagnetic waves.

100
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:55,625
And that’s this place?

101
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:57,291
She’s here.

102
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:58,666
I’m sure of it.

103
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,166
[rumbling]

104
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:02,666
[footsteps]

105
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:06,291
[gasp]
Behind us!

106
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,666
[grunt, sigh]

107
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:09,625
[footsteps]

108
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:10,833
[growl]

109
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:12,583
Something’s set up
to hold them off.

110
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:14,041
Mage must be using the device

111
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:16,375
that she got from Cassiel
to keep the DZs at bay.

112
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:19,291
Then that’s proof that
she’s definitely here.

113
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,875
But if we continue
any further,

114
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:24,916
we might not be
able to turn back.

115
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,500
[whimper]

116
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,333
[sigh]

117
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,916
[DERRIDA]
She’ll need to filter out noise.

118
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,583
So I would guess,

119
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,416
she’s down in the basement.

120
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,083
[YURI grunts]

121
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:42,791
-[MAYUKA] Papa!
-Hmm? What’s up?

122
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,750
Uh. Um...

123
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,916
Well, it’s just...

124
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,166
[VIDAUX]
Hmm...

125
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:51,375
[MAYUKA sighs]

126
00:07:52,375 --> 00:07:53,875
Mmm...

127
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:57,250
While we were driving here,
I thought up a story.

128
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:59,583
When you come back,
can I tell you it?

129
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,416
[gasp]

130
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,833
Yeah.

131
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:04,708
Course you can, sweetheart.

132
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,000
[whimper]

133
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:11,791
[rumble]

134
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,625
-[jets humming, air rushing]
-[grunts]

135
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:18,750
[YURI]
Oh no!

136
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,333
[SCHMIDT laughing on speaker]

137
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:23,291
[SCHMIDT]
End of the line, you lot!

138
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:26,250
If you want this to go smoothly,
give yourselves up!

139
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,750
[jets humming]

140
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:28,958
He found us!

141
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:30,958
You don’t need Derrida anymore!

142
00:08:31,041 --> 00:08:33,875
[SCHMIDT] That’s where
you’re wrong, Miss Yuri.

143
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:36,291
With his cooperation,
we’ll have a massive advantage

144
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:38,250
once the war is over.

145
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:39,333
No way!

146
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:40,458
[chuckle]

147
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:42,875
Guess negotiations broke down.

148
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:45,833
Release the Xs.

149
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,125
-[KATZE] Yes, sir!
-[chuckle]

150
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:49,458
[doors open]

151
00:08:49,541 --> 00:08:50,750
[whirring]

152
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,041
[beeping]

153
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:53,000
♪

154
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:54,666
What?

155
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:57,125
[SCHMIDT] Behold! The future
form of the DZs you invented!

156
00:08:57,208 --> 00:09:00,250
They are the true
ultimate weapons!

157
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:01,916
[DERRIDA]
Those are DZs?!

158
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,458
[chuckling]

159
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:07,375
-Alright, let’s dance, boys.
-[snap]

160
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:10,666
[buzzing, whirring]

161
00:09:13,541 --> 00:09:14,458
[YURI whimpering]

162
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:15,916
[DERRIDA]
Damn.

163
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,541
-Ah!
-[energy buzzing]

164
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:21,208
[blast]

165
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:22,291
-[explosion]
-[grunt]

166
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:23,708
[yell]

167
00:09:23,791 --> 00:09:25,458
[thud, crack]

168
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:27,333
[gasp]
No good?

169
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:30,166
Why’d they have to go
and develop these things?

170
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,125
[gunfire]

171
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:33,500
Charge me extra! Just shoot!

172
00:09:33,583 --> 00:09:36,250
♪

173
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,625
[blasting, explosions]

174
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,375
[gasp]
The device!

175
00:09:42,458 --> 00:09:44,083
[creaking]

176
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,875
[beeping, buzzing]

177
00:09:53,166 --> 00:09:54,625
No!

178
00:09:54,708 --> 00:09:56,625
And right when we were so
close to reaching Mage, too.

179
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:02,333
[smashing]

180
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:03,416
[gasp]

181
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,583
[BOTH gasp]

182
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:06,041
[tires screech]

183
00:10:06,125 --> 00:10:07,791
-[YURI] Mayuka?
-[VIDAUX] What’re you doing?!

184
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,458
[MAYUKA]
It wasn’t me!

185
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:12,375
Graham just started driving
and told me to get out, I swear!

186
00:10:12,458 --> 00:10:13,458
What?

187
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:15,458
[GRAHAM]
Master, leave this to me.

188
00:10:15,541 --> 00:10:16,916
I can only do this once,

189
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,208
but I have overclocked
all my functions.

190
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:23,416
Derrida, I may not exist
in the future that you create.

191
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:26,083
But, for now...

192
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,333
I must choose the best path.

193
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:29,833
-[VIDAUX] What do you mean?!
-[gasp]

194
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:31,875
[GRAHAM]
Master, Mayuka...

195
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,541
It has been a fine journey.

196
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:35,833
Thank you for all of
the stories you have given me.

197
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:37,791
-[MAYUKA] Graham!
-[VIDAUX] Wait!

198
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:39,875
-[engine roar]
-[dust flying]

199
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:42,916
[engine roar]

200
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,083
[smashing]

201
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:50,375
♪

202
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,041
[bang, tires screech]

203
00:10:52,125 --> 00:10:53,875
[gasp, growl]

204
00:10:53,958 --> 00:10:55,166
Destroy that thing, now!

205
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:58,166
[rapid beeping]

206
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,916
[beeping continues to speed up]

207
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:04,000
[slow beeping]

208
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,333
[explosion]

209
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:07,791
[ALL gasp]

210
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,458
Oh no, Graham!

211
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:11,250
-[groaning]
-[metal breaking]

212
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,708
No, please, come back!

213
00:11:18,791 --> 00:11:20,250
-[whimpering]
-[blasting]

214
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:21,958
-[smash]
-[grunt]

215
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,083
[MAYUKA whimpers]

216
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:24,750
[VIDAUX]
Derrida, leave this to me.

217
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,125
-Get moving!
-Huh?

218
00:11:27,125 --> 00:11:28,750
-Take her.
-[MAYUKA] Huh?

219
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:31,583
-Papa...
-I will.

220
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:34,041
No, you can’t stay!
You have to come, too!

221
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:36,500
[VIDAUX]
I’ll catch up with you.

222
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:38,833
[gasp]
Promise me!

223
00:11:38,916 --> 00:11:41,416
♪

224
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:42,333
[click]

225
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:45,791
[gun whirs]

226
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:52,291
They won’t get away!
[laugh]

227
00:11:52,375 --> 00:11:53,833
[beeping]

228
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:56,750
[gunfire]

229
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,875
-[blasting]
-[groan]

230
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,250
[sigh]
Let’s try this.

231
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:03,541
[grunt]

232
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:05,791
-Come on baby, work!
-[hydraulics whir]

233
00:12:07,458 --> 00:12:09,625
-[yelling]
-[firing]

234
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:13,875
[DERRIDA straining]

235
00:12:15,541 --> 00:12:17,583
[grunting, groaning]

236
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,500
[panting]
No use.

237
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,583
[growling]

238
00:12:24,666 --> 00:12:26,208
We’ll go around.

239
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:31,083
[breeze blowing]

240
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:32,583
[YURI gasps]

241
00:12:32,666 --> 00:12:34,208
Mayuka...

242
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:38,041
Don’t let go of
the hand rail, okay?

243
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:40,000
Sure!

244
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:42,083
[wind blowing]

245
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,916
-[machines humming]
-Hmm? [gasp]

246
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,916
[KATZE] Enough of this
foolish resistance!

247
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,583
[HUND]
Come along with us quietly.

248
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:53,000
[DERRIDA]
C’mon! We gotta run!

249
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,166
[SCHMIDT] Yvain is
the only one we need alive!

250
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:56,208
Yes, sir.

251
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:58,041
[blasting]

252
00:12:58,125 --> 00:12:59,083
[YURI]
Ah!

253
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:00,958
-[gasp]
-[gasp] Yuri!

254
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:04,041
♪

255
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,541
[heavy breathing]

256
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:15,291
Just keep going!
Mage is waiting!

257
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,875
What are you saying?

258
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:19,416
Yuri, you can jump this,
I know that you can!

259
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,833
[SCHMIDT]
Feel free to kill the girl.

260
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:21,708
Roger that.

261
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:23,416
Yuri! I’ll catch you!

262
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:26,708
Dummy, you really
don’t get it, do you?

263
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:28,666
[beeping]

264
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,541
[YURI]
Okay, here I go!

265
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:31,458
[gunfire]

266
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:33,166
[screaming]

267
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,625
[BOTH grunt]

268
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:36,833
[whirring]

269
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,083
[YURI panting]

270
00:13:38,166 --> 00:13:40,208
-You okay?
-[YURI] Yeah.

271
00:13:40,291 --> 00:13:42,083
Let’s keep moving.

272
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:43,708
[DERRIDA]
Right.

273
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,666
[gasping]

274
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:52,041
[GIRLS gasp]

275
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,375
[whirring]

276
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:55,583
[KATZE]
Derrida Yvain.

277
00:13:55,666 --> 00:13:57,833
There’s no escape,
just surrender.

278
00:13:57,916 --> 00:13:59,833
Damn it all.

279
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,750
We were so close.

280
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:05,791
[explosion]

281
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:08,000
[gasp, gurgle]

282
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:13,875
[slice]

283
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:18,666
[splatter]

284
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,958
[heavy breathing]

285
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:24,416
I won’t let anyone...
take it from me.

286
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,000
[gasp]

287
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,333
[DONNA]
I’ll be the one to kill you...

288
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,458
Me!

289
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:33,041
Donna...

290
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:41,958
♪

291
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,625
[grunt, growl]

292
00:15:01,708 --> 00:15:03,625
-[footsteps]
-[grunt]

293
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:04,666
[heavy breathing]

294
00:15:05,666 --> 00:15:06,458
[grunt]

295
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:09,125
[straining]
Huh?

296
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:12,000
[DONNA gasping, groaning]

297
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,791
[pained breathing]

298
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:18,333
[BOTH grunt]

299
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,833
Donna! No, Angelica!

300
00:15:21,916 --> 00:15:23,208
I heard about the experiment.

301
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:26,750
-[heavy breathing]
-[slice]

302
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:30,833
I finally understand why
you hate me so much, okay?

303
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:32,291
[DONNA]
Then answer me this.

304
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:34,916
Why did you create
something like me?

305
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,666
Something like you?

306
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:40,166
Answer!

307
00:15:41,791 --> 00:15:42,583
[BOTH grunt]

308
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:43,833
-[gasp]
-Derrida!

309
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:46,458
[groaning]

310
00:15:48,541 --> 00:15:49,416
[panting]

311
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,125
-Answer me, Yvain.
-[slice]

312
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,208
Why do humans create
things in their image

313
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:55,791
that can never be
human themselves?

314
00:15:56,791 --> 00:15:57,875
-[grunt]
-[growl]

315
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:00,250
Tell me why!

316
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:01,500
[heavy breathing]

317
00:16:01,583 --> 00:16:02,416
[grunt]

318
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,791
-[thud]
-Ah!

319
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:05,041
[groan]

320
00:16:05,125 --> 00:16:07,291
You’re saying
Angelica lost her life

321
00:16:07,375 --> 00:16:09,750
because of a worthless
maggot like you?!

322
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:11,958
[DERRIDA grunt, groaning]

323
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:14,041
[DERRIDA gasping]

324
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,041
-[coughing]
-[panting]

325
00:16:18,125 --> 00:16:19,416
[DERRIDA]
You’re wrong!

326
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,250
Listen. You are Angelica!

327
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:24,875
My name is and always
has been Donna!

328
00:16:24,958 --> 00:16:27,250
I’m a mechanical puppet
that you people designed!

329
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,250
Then why do you hate me?

330
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:30,291
[gasp]

331
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:32,666
Machines aren’t built to feel.

332
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:35,708
Automata 2058 may
have called you Donna,

333
00:16:35,791 --> 00:16:38,750
but it wasn’t programmed
to experience any emotions!

334
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,250
[wind blowing]

335
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,958
[2058, voices overlapping]
This is your family...

336
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:44,791
Get a grip on yourself,
Donna. I am Angelica...

337
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,083
Your panic...
Why wouldn’t I know...

338
00:16:46,166 --> 00:16:48,750
How do you feel about
the name Donna...?

339
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:51,916
[slice]

340
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,166
Are you saying that...

341
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:56,916
I’m Angelica? But I...

342
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,166
You are clearly human!
If you were really a machine,

343
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:01,916
then you wouldn’t have
these emotions!

344
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,083
Impossible!

345
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:05,625
How dare you lie about this,

346
00:17:05,708 --> 00:17:07,750
when you’re the reason
Angelica is dead!

347
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:08,833
[DERRIDA]
It’s not a lie!

348
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:10,625
Try to remember, Angelica!

349
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:11,958
You are a human being!

350
00:17:12,041 --> 00:17:13,250
Be quiet!

351
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,250
-Ah!
-[splatter]

352
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,500
-[yelp]
-[gasp]

353
00:17:15,583 --> 00:17:17,125
[pained groaning]

354
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:18,041
[BOTH gasp]

355
00:17:18,125 --> 00:17:20,625
[DONNA screaming]

356
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,333
You’re lying!
[gasp]

357
00:17:23,416 --> 00:17:25,083
Angelica was a pathetic woman

358
00:17:25,166 --> 00:17:26,500
killed during
a simple experiment

359
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:28,708
she should have been
able to handle!

360
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:31,500
[gasp]
She and I aren’t the same!

361
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:33,333
I’m very sorry about
that experiment,

362
00:17:33,416 --> 00:17:34,666
and what it did to you.

363
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:36,208
-[scream]
-But I promise,

364
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:38,625
I never meant for anything
like this to happen!

365
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:39,500
[gasping]

366
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:42,583
♪

367
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:53,250
[gasp]

368
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:57,333
[robotic voice] What else
could it be but Angelica?

369
00:17:57,416 --> 00:18:00,416
[fire crackling]

370
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:08,750
[gasping]

371
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:15,333
My name has always been...

372
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:16,500
Donna.

373
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:18,041
I am merely a machine,

374
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:20,041
created by man.

375
00:18:21,791 --> 00:18:23,916
Answer me, Yvain.

376
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:27,625
Why create things
in your image,

377
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:29,958
that can never be like you,

378
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:32,708
no matter how hard they try?

379
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:34,916
Tell me,

380
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,916
why did you hurt Angelica?

381
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:42,333
You know,
you’re like me. A scientist.

382
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:45,125
We do what we do to make
the world a better place.

383
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,416
That’s what your
experiment was, too.

384
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,958
♪

385
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:52,750
[DONNA]
But you only birthed tragedy.

386
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:56,958
The price of progress.

387
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:58,625
If no one had thought
to use science

388
00:18:58,708 --> 00:19:01,416
to give machines personalities,

389
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,750
I could have remained Angelica.

390
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:06,333
[gasp]

391
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:07,666
[sigh]

392
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:10,666
[DONNA]
I see it happening.

393
00:19:11,708 --> 00:19:13,791
I see people like you,

394
00:19:13,875 --> 00:19:15,375
forever creating new things

395
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:18,208
to satisfy the greed
of those in power.

396
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:22,625
Glory, prestige,
ambition, pride.

397
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:25,833
You’ll create anything
for anyone who’ll pay,

398
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,666
never thinking of
how they’ll be used,

399
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:31,041
or what misery and despair
they’ll bring about.

400
00:19:32,541 --> 00:19:35,166
The advancement of science
can lead to tragedy.

401
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,208
That’s just a risk we take.

402
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:38,916
But still, if we as a people

403
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,875
stop taking those steps forward,

404
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,541
then all progress stops.

405
00:19:42,625 --> 00:19:44,208
We’d close off our future!

406
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:48,875
To move forward with that
burden on our shoulders,

407
00:19:48,958 --> 00:19:50,625
that’s what it
means to be human.

408
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,500
♪

409
00:19:52,583 --> 00:19:54,000
[sigh]

410
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:56,291
So you’ll allow your
egos to lead this world

411
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,166
to ruin on principle.

412
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:01,625
And I can only watch...

413
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:03,541
[sob]

414
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:04,916
[gasp]

415
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,833
[breeze blowing]

416
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:24,750
[sigh]

417
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:27,833
[breeze blowing]

418
00:20:33,208 --> 00:20:34,208
[click]

419
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:38,291
[sighs]
We’re almost there.

420
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:40,041
Are you sure we
can’t turn back now?

421
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:41,333
Huh?

422
00:20:41,416 --> 00:20:42,500
[MAYUKA]
But, why?

423
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:45,541
Derrida, when you do find Mage,

424
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:47,875
you’ll go back in time
and change the world?

425
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,458
Yeah.

426
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:52,541
[YURI] And once it’s changed,
all this will be gone!

427
00:20:52,625 --> 00:20:53,875
[YURI gasps]

428
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:56,166
Are you okay with that?

429
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:59,333
I have no way to know
if this is right.

430
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:01,708
But, if I don’t do it,
I’ll always regret it.

431
00:21:02,708 --> 00:21:03,833
So, I must.

432
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:06,416
[sigh]

433
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:07,875
-[groan]
-[door opens]

434
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:16,541
[YURI]
Huh? Mayuka?

435
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:18,875
Aren’t you coming with us?

436
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,166
Come on now.

437
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:22,750
[sigh]

438
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,875
Big Sis, you go on.

439
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:27,291
I've decided that I’m
gonna go back to Papa.

440
00:21:27,375 --> 00:21:28,875
[YURI]
Huh?

441
00:21:28,958 --> 00:21:30,958
If the world's gonna
change no matter what,

442
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:34,125
then I wanna stay with Papa
until everything goes poof!

443
00:21:34,208 --> 00:21:35,541
Mayuka...

444
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:37,083
♪

445
00:21:37,166 --> 00:21:38,416
Be careful, okay?

446
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:40,750
Hmm?

447
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:41,625
Mm-hmm!

448
00:21:41,708 --> 00:21:44,458
Bye-bye, Derrida, Yuri!

449
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:46,375
I believe in you!

450
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:48,541
-[door closes]
-[YURI gasps, sighs]

451
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:52,541
[sigh]

452
00:21:53,541 --> 00:21:54,541
[panting]

453
00:21:57,041 --> 00:21:58,541
[elevator rumble]

